---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHeader from "../components/PageHeader.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="About">
  <PageHeader eyebrow="Shariq Hirani" title="About" />

  <div class="about-prose pb-16">
    <p>
      Senior Solutions Engineer at GitHub, founder, and habitual builder. I write here about the work and the in-between — shipping software, the teams that build it, and the AI shift happening in real time.
    </p>

    <p>
      I've spent over a decade in engineering — across architecture, distributed systems, infrastructure, and platform — moving between hands-on building and leading teams, and lately shipping my own products. The themes I keep coming back to:
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>How engineering teams <em>actually</em> run, vs how they're written about.</li>
      <li>The line between shipping fast and shipping right — and why most of the disagreement here is really about risk tolerance, not technique.</li>
      <li>What AI tooling looks like when it holds up under real, sustained use — not demos, not press releases.</li>
      <li>Career arcs in tech: the asymmetric leap from senior engineer to lead, and the under-discussed move <em>back</em> down the ladder when leadership stops fitting.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      Lately I'm building <a href="https://lognote.dev">lognote</a> (local transcription and summarization for meetings) and a few other things over on <a href="/projects">projects</a>.
    </p>
  </div>

  <style is:global>
    @reference "../styles/global.css";
    .about-prose {
      @apply max-w-prose font-sans text-[16px] leading-[1.7];
    }
    .about-prose p { @apply my-5; }
    .about-prose ul { @apply my-5 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6; }
    .about-prose a {
      @apply underline decoration-[var(--accent)] decoration-2 underline-offset-4 transition-colors;
    }
    .about-prose a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
    .about-prose em { @apply italic; }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
